        "id": 1161844
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-27T01:32:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would not expect Go to do that automatically, being the type of language it is.\n\nWould that be TLS compression?  I can\u0027t think of any other transport compression that would be commonly added under HTTP.  TLS compression is vulnerable to attacks like CRIME, so it would be surprising in a bad way if Go added that silently.\n\nI took a quick look but didn\u0027t see anything https://godoc.org/crypto/tls#Config",
      "parentUuid": "c9204afa_ea6eadad",
      "revId": "f82df52a6a4133d5b27a8ef01dddcfe19cabb3a1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
